<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<div style="text-align: center;"><img alt="" src="logo.jpg"></div>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:12pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>N</b><b>otice of the </b><b>20</b><b>20</b><b> </b><b>Annual Meeting of Shareholders</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:12pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>to be Held on </b><b>Thursday,</b><b> May </b><b>14</b><b>, </b><b>20</b><b>20</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Annual Meeting of Shareholders (the &#8220;Annual Meeting&#8221;) of Apple Hospitality REIT, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) will be held at the Courtyard and Residence Inn Richmond Downtown, located at 1320 East Cary Street, Richmond, Virginia 23219, on Thursday,&nbsp;May 14, 2020 at 10:00 a.m., Eastern Daylight Time, for the following purposes: &nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9.35pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="width:36pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width:36pt;vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">1.</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">To elect eight (8) directors named in the attached proxy statement to the Board of Directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221;);</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="width:36pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width:36pt;vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">2.</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">To consider and act on an advisory vote regarding the approval of compensation paid to certain executive officers by the Company;</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="width:36pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width:36pt;vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">3.</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">To ratify the appointment of Ernst &amp; Young LLP as the Company&#8217;s independent registered public accounting firm to serve for 2020, and;</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="width:36pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width:36pt;vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">4.</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">To transact such other business as may properly come before the meeting.</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0.1pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:35.9pt;">If you were a holder of record of any common shares of the Company at the close of business on the record date of March 20, 2020, you are entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting.&nbsp;If you are present at the Annual Meeting, you may vote in person even if you have previously returned a proxy card.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0.1pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:35.9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0.1pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:35.9pt;">While we currently intend to hold the Annual Meeting in person, we are continuing to monitor the coronavirus (COVID-19) situation. We are sensitive to the public health and travel concerns our shareholders may have and the restrictions that federal, state and local governments may impose. In the event it is not possible or advisable to hold the Annual Meeting in person, we will, as promptly as practicable, announce any alternative meeting arrangements, which may include holding the meeting by means of remote communication (i.e., virtual meeting). We encourage you to monitor our investor relations website at www.applehospitalityreit.com for any updates regarding the Annual Meeting.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company is furnishing its proxy statement, proxy and 2019 Annual Report on Form 10-K (the &#8220;Annual Report&#8221;) to you electronically via the Internet, instead of mailing printed copies of those materials to each shareholder. The Company has sent to its shareholders a Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials that provides instructions on how to access its proxy materials on the Internet, how you can request and receive a paper copy of the proxy statement, Annual Report and proxy for the Annual Meeting and future meetings of shareholders, and how to vote online at www.proxyvote.com. Shareholders can also call 1-800-579-1639 to request proxy materials or 1-800-690-6903 to vote by telephone. Additionally, this proxy statement and the Annual Report are available at http://materials.proxyvote.com/03784Y. Please read the enclosed information carefully before submitting your proxy.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">If you have any questions or need assistance in voting your shares, please call Ms. Kelly Clarke in the Company&#8217;s Investor Relations Department, at (804) 344-8121.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">By Order of the Board of Directors</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0pt;"><img src="aple20200321_def14aimg002.jpg" style="width: 154pt; height: 46pt;"></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><b>April&nbsp;</b><b>1</b><b>, </b><b>20</b><b>20</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;"><b>REGARDLESS OF THE NUMBER OF SHARES YOU HOLD, AS A SHAREHOLDER YOUR ROLE IS VERY IMPORTANT, AND THE BOARD STRONGLY ENCOURAGES YOU TO EXERCISE YOUR RIGHT TO VOTE.</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>WHETHER OR NOT YOU EXPECT TO BE PRESENT AT THE MEETING, PLEASE VOTE ONLINE, BY PHONE OR BY SIGNING, DATING AND RETURNING THE PROXY CARD.&nbsp;IF YOU ATTEND THE MEETING, YOU MAY WITHDRAW YOUR PROXY AND VOTE IN PERSON.</b>&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>APPLE HOSPITALITY REIT, INC.</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>PROXY STATEMENT</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>DATED</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>APRIL&nbsp;</b><b>1</b><b>, </b><b>20</b><b>20</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>ANNUAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>TO BE HELD ON </b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>MAY </b><b>1</b><b>4</b><b>, </b><b>20</b><b>20</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><a id="General" name="General"><b>General</b></a></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The enclosed proxy is solicited by the Board of Directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221; or &#8220;Board of Directors&#8221;) of Apple Hospitality REIT, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221; or &#8220;Apple Hospitality&#8221;) for the Annual Meeting of Shareholders to be held at the Courtyard and Residence Inn Richmond Downtown, located at 1320 East Cary Street, Richmond, Virginia 23219, on Thursday, May 14, 2020<b>&nbsp;</b>at 10:00 a.m., Eastern Daylight Time<b>&nbsp;</b>(the &#8220;Annual Meeting&#8221;). Your proxy may be revoked at any time before being voted at the Annual Meeting, either by a written notice of revocation that is received by the Company before the Annual Meeting or by conduct that is inconsistent with the continued effectiveness of the proxy, such as delivering another proxy with a later date or attending the Annual Meeting and voting in person.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Unless your proxy indicates otherwise, all shares represented by a proxy that you sign and return will be voted <b>FOR</b> the nominees listed in proposal 1, <b>FOR</b> proposals 2 and 3, and in accordance with the best judgment of the proxy holders for any other matters properly brought before the Annual Meeting.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Record holders of the Company&#8217;s common shares (the &#8220;Common Shares&#8221;) at the close of business on March 20, 2020 (the &#8220;Record Date&#8221;) are entitled to notice of, and to vote at, the Annual Meeting.&nbsp;This proxy statement, the Company&#8217;s 2019 Annual Report on Form 10-K, which includes the Company&#8217;s audited consolidated financial statements for the year ended December 31, 2019 (the &#8220;Annual Report&#8221;), and the proxy card are first being made available, and a notice and electronic delivery of the proxy materials (the &#8220;Notice of Internet Availability&#8221;) is first being mailed, to shareholders on or about April 1, 2020.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">As permitted by the rules of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#8220;SEC&#8221; or &#8220;Securities and Exchange Commission&#8221;), the Company is making this proxy statement and its Annual Report available to its shareholders electronically via the Internet. The Company believes that this process expedites receipt of its proxy materials by shareholders, while lowering the costs and reducing the environmental impact of the Annual Meeting. If you received the Notice of Internet Availability by mail, you will not receive a printed copy of the proxy materials in the mail. Instead, the Notice of Internet Availability instructs you on how to access and review all of the important information contained in the proxy statement and Annual Report. The Notice of Internet Availability also instructs you on how you may submit your proxy over the Internet. If you received a Notice of Internet Availability by mail and would like to receive a printed copy of the proxy materials, please follow the instructions for requesting printed materials contained in the Notice of Internet Availability.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">At the close of business on the Record Date, a total of&nbsp;223,317,081 Common Shares were issued and outstanding and entitled to vote on all matters, including those to be acted upon at the Annual Meeting.&nbsp;Each Common Share is entitled to one vote.&nbsp;The presence in person or by proxy of a majority of the Common Shares entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting will constitute a quorum for the transaction of business.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">In the event that a quorum is not present at the Annual Meeting, it is expected the meeting will be adjourned or postponed to solicit additional proxies.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9.35pt;"><b><a id="Solicitation" name="Solicitation">Solicitation</a> of Proxies</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company will be responsible for the costs of the solicitation set forth in this proxy statement. Brokerage houses, fiduciaries, nominees and others will be reimbursed for their out-of-pocket expenses in forwarding proxy materials to beneficial owners of Common Shares.&nbsp;In addition to soliciting proxies by mail, certain of the Company&#8217;s directors, officers and employees may solicit proxies by telephone, personal contact, or other means of communication.&nbsp;No additional compensation, except for reimbursement of reasonable out-of-pocket expenses, will be paid to directors, officers and employees of the Company in connection with the solicitation.&nbsp;Any questions or requests for assistance regarding this proxy solicitation may be directed to the Company by telephone at (804) 344-8121, Attention: Investor Relations, or your bank, broker or other custodian that holds your shares. Notice of revocation of proxies should be sent to Broadridge Financial Services, Inc., 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, New York 11717, Attn: Issuer Services Department.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="CompanyInfo" name="CompanyInfo">Company Info</a>rmation</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company operates as a real estate investment trust (&#8220;REIT&#8221;) for federal income tax purposes.&nbsp;The mailing address of the Company is 814 East Main Street, Richmond, Virginia 23219.&nbsp;The Company can be contacted, and public information about the Company can be obtained, by sending a written notice to Ms. Kelly Clarke, Investor Relations Department, at the Company&#8217;s address as provided above or through its website, www.applehospitalityreit.com.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company&#8217;s Annual Report and its other public federal securities filings also may be obtained electronically through the EDGAR system of the Securities and Exchange Commission at www.sec.gov.&nbsp;The proxy materials are available at http://materials.proxyvote.com/03784Y.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="Ownership" name="Ownership">Ownership</a> of </b><b>Certain Beneficial Owners and Manag</b><b>e</b><b>ment</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">As discussed in &#8220;Corporate Governance, Risk Oversight and Procedures for Shareholder Communications&#8212;Share Ownership Guidelines,&#8221; the Company has adopted share ownership guidelines for its Board of Directors and named executive officers. The determination of &#8220;beneficial ownership&#8221; for purposes of this proxy statement has been based on information reported to the Company and the rules and regulations of the Securities and Exchange Commission.&nbsp;References below to &#8220;beneficial ownership&#8221; by a particular person, and similar references, should not be construed as an admission or determination by the Company that Common Shares in fact are beneficially owned by such person.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The following table sets forth information regarding the beneficial ownership of the Company&#8217;s Common Shares as of March 20, 2020 with respect to (a) each current director and director nominee, (b) each named executive officer, (c) all of the Company&#8217;s directors and executive officers as a group and (d) each person known by the Company to be the beneficial owner of greater than a 5% interest in the Company&#8217;s Common Shares. Unless otherwise indicated, all Common Shares are owned directly and the indicated person has sole voting and investment power, and the address of each named person is c/o Apple Hospitality REIT, Inc., 814 East Main Street, Richmond, Virginia 23219.</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:18pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;"><b><a id="Proposals" name="Proposals">Proposals</a> to be Voted </b><b>Up</b><b>on</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;"><i>&nbsp;</i></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 18pt;"><i><a id="Proposal1" name="Proposal1">Proposal 1.</a> </i><i> </i><i>Election of Directors</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company&#8217;s Board of Directors currently consists of eight directors, all of whom are standing for re-election at the Annual Meeting. The Board of Directors recommends their re-election to the Board of Directors to serve as directors until the 2021 annual meeting of shareholders or until their successors are duly elected and qualified, except in the event of prior resignation, death or removal.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Unless otherwise specified, all Common Shares represented by proxies will be voted <b>FOR</b> the election of the nominees listed below.&nbsp;If a nominee ceases to be available for election as a director, discretionary authority may be exercised by each of the proxies named on the attached proxy card to vote for a substitute.&nbsp;No circumstances are presently known that would cause any nominee to be unavailable for election as a director.&nbsp;The nominees are now members of the Board of Directors, have been nominated by action of the Board of Directors, and have indicated their willingness to serve if elected.&nbsp;If a quorum is present at the Annual Meeting, the positions on the Board of Directors will be filled by the election of the properly nominated candidates who receive the greatest number of votes at the Annual Meeting, even if a nominee does not receive a majority of all votes represented and entitled to be cast.&nbsp;Under the Company&#8217;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, if an incumbent director fails to receive at least a majority of the votes cast, such director will tender his or her resignation from the Board of Directors. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee of the Board will consider, and determine whether to accept, such resignation and make a recommendation to the Board of Directors.&nbsp;Within 90 days of the certification of the election results, the Board of Directors must act on the resignation, taking into consideration any recommendation by the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and any additional relevant factors.&nbsp;A director who tenders his or her resignation does not participate in the decisions of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee or the Board relating to the resignation.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">A shareholder who wishes to abstain from voting on the election of a director may do so by specifying, as provided on the proxy, that authority to vote for any or all of the nominees is to be withheld.&nbsp;Withheld votes and broker non-votes will have no effect on the election of a director.&nbsp;A broker non-vote occurs when the entity holding shares in street name has not received voting instructions from the beneficial owner and either chooses not to vote those shares on a routine matter at the shareholders meeting or is not permitted to vote those shares on a non-routine matter.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:18pt;"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:18pt;"><b>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECOMMENDS A VOTE &#8220;</b><b><u>FOR</u></b><b>&#8221; </b><b>EACH OF </b><b>THE NOMINEES.</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The following is a snapshot of the Company&#8217;s Board composition:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; width: 100%;">

		<tr>
			<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 12pt;"><b>Average Tenure of 5 Years</b></td>
			<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 12pt;"><b>Gender Diversity</b></td>
		</tr>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: center;"><b>Director Independence</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:12pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;"><b>Board Skills</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:12pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;text-indent:0;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="vertical-align: bottom; width: 16%; border-bottom: thin solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;"><b>Leadership</b></p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: bottom; width: 1%;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: bottom; width: 15%; border-bottom: thin solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;"><b>Financial</b></p>
			</td>

Mr. Knight was also the founder of each of the Apple REIT Companies and served as their Chairman and Chief Executive Officer from their inception until the companies were sold to a third party or merged with the Company, as described in Note 1 below. In addition, Mr. Knight served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Cornerstone Realty Income Trust, Inc., a REIT, from 1993 until it merged with Colonial Properties Trust, a REIT, in 2005. Following the merger in 2005 until April 2011, Mr. Knight served as a trustee of Colonial Properties Trust. Cornerstone Realty Income Trust, Inc. owned and operated apartment communities in Virginia, North Carolina, South Carolina, Georgia and Texas. Mr. Knight is a partner and Chief Executive Officer of Energy 11 GP, LLC, the general partner of Energy 11, L.P., and Energy Resources 12 GP, LLC, the general partner of Energy Resources 12, L.P., partnerships focused on investments in the oil and gas industry. Mr. Knight is the founding Chairman of Southern Virginia University in Buena Vista, Virginia.&nbsp;He also is a member of the Advisory Board to the Graduate School of Real Estate and Urban Land Development at Virginia Commonwealth University.&nbsp;Additionally, he serves on the National Advisory Council for Brigham Young University and is a founding member of the University&#8217;s Entrepreneurial Department of the Graduate School of Business Management. The&nbsp;Board of Directors believes his extensive REIT executive experience and extensive background in real estate, corporate finance and strategic planning, as well as his entrepreneurial background, provide him with the skills and qualifications to serve as a director.&nbsp;&nbsp;On February 12, 2014, Mr. Knight, Apple Seven, Apple Eight, Apple Nine and their related advisory companies entered into settlement agreements with the SEC.&nbsp;&nbsp;Along with Apple Seven, Apple Eight, Apple Nine and their advisory companies, and without admitting or denying the SEC&#8217;s allegations, Mr. Knight consented to the entry of an administrative order, under which Mr. Knight and the noted companies each agreed to cease and desist from committing or causing any violations of Sections 13(a), 13(b)(2)(A), 13(b)(2)(B), 14(a), and 16(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;) and Rules 12b-20, 13a-1, 13a-13, 13a-14, 14a-9, and 16a-3 thereunder.</p>

Knight is the father of Justin G. Knight, the Company&#8217;s Chief Executive Officer, and Nelson G. Knight, the Company&#8217;s President, Real Estate and Investments.</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Age: </b>63</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Director Since:</b> 2018</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Committees: </b>Nominating and Corporate Governance (Chair)</p>
			</td>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">Ms. McGarvie was a member of the faculty of Harvard Business School, teaching in the accounting and management department from July 2012 to June 2014. Ms. McGarvie served as Chief Executive Officer and Founder of Leadership for International Finance, LLC, an advisory firm offering consulting services and providing leadership seminars, from 2003 to 2012, where she offered strategic reviews and leadership seminars for improved decision-making for corporate and academic groups. From 1999 to 2002, Ms. McGarvie was the Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of BIC Group, a publicly&nbsp;traded consumer goods company with operations in 36 countries. Prior to that, Ms. McGarvie served as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Hannaford Bros. Co., a Fortune 500 retailer. Ms. McGarvie currently serves on the boards of directors of LKQ Corporation (&#8220;LKQ&#8221;), Sonoco Products Company (&#8220;Sonoco&#8221;) and Wawa, Inc., and previously served on the boards of directors of Accenture plc, Viacom Inc., Pepsi Bottling Group, Inc., The Travelers Companies, Inc. and Lafarge North America. She serves as chair of the LKQ Audit Committee and a member of its Governance/Nominating Committee and as chair of the Financial Policy Committee and a member of&nbsp;the Audit&nbsp;Committee and Executive Compensation Committee for Sonoco. Ms. McGarvie is</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>Director </i><i>Retirement</i>. Effective December 6, 2019, Mr. Bruce H. Matson retired from the Board of Directors of the Company. Mr. Matson had been a member of the Board since 2008. When he retired, Mr. Matson was the Chair of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and served on the Executive Committee. Following this development, pursuant to the Company&#8217;s bylaws, the Board reduced the size of the Board of Directors to eight.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 18pt;"><i><a id="Proposal2" name="Proposal2">Proposal 2</a>. </i><i> </i><i>Advisory Vote On Executive Compensation Paid by the Company</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">In accordance with Section 14A of the Exchange Act, the Company is providing its shareholders with the opportunity to approve, on a non-binding, advisory basis, the compensation paid to the Company&#8217;s named executive officers as disclosed in this proxy statement.&nbsp;The Board of Directors has adopted a policy, which shareholders approved by a non-binding advisory vote, of providing for an annual &#8220;say-on-pay&#8221; advisory vote. The Company encourages shareholders to read the disclosure under &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#8221; for more information concerning the Company&#8217;s compensation philosophy, programs and practices, the compensation and governance-related actions taken in fiscal 2019 and the compensation paid to the named executive officers.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Accordingly, the Company is asking you to approve the adoption of the following resolution:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">RESOLVED: That the shareholders of the Company approve, on a non-binding, advisory basis, the compensation paid to the Company&#8217;s named executive officers, as disclosed pursuant to Item 402 of Regulation S-K, including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, compensation tables and narrative discussion in the proxy statement.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The affirmative vote of a majority of the votes cast will be necessary to approve this proposal.&nbsp;Abstentions and broker non-votes will have no effect on the outcome of this proposal.&nbsp;The shareholder vote on this proposal is advisory and non-binding and serves only as a recommendation to the Board of Directors. Although the vote is non-binding, the Compensation Committee and the Board of Directors value the opinions of shareholders and will consider the outcome of the vote when making future compensation decisions.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECOMMENDS A VOTE &#8220;</b><b><u>FOR</u></b><b>&#8221; THE ABOVE PROPOSAL.</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt 0.1pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 18pt;"><a id="Proposal3" name="Proposal3"><i>Proposal </i><i>3</i></a><i>. Ratification of the Appointment of Ernst &amp; Young LLP as the Company&#8217;s Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The firm of Ernst &amp; Young LLP served as the independent registered public accounting firm for the Company in 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;A representative of Ernst &amp; Young LLP is expected to be present at the Annual Meeting.&nbsp;The representative will have an opportunity to make a statement if he or she so desires and will be available to answer appropriate questions from shareholders.&nbsp;The Board of</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">All services rendered by Ernst &amp; Young LLP are permissible under applicable laws and regulations, and the annual audit of the Company was pre-approved by the Audit Committee, as required by applicable law.&nbsp;The nature of each of the services categorized in the preceding table is described below:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>Audit Fees</i>. These are fees for professional services rendered for the audit of the Company&#8217;s annual financial statements included in the Company&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K, reviews of the financial statements included in the Company&#8217;s Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q, or services normally provided by the independent auditor in connection with statutory or regulatory filings or engagements, and other accounting and financial reporting work necessary to comply with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (&#8220;PCAOB&#8221;) and fees for services that only the Company&#8217;s independent auditor can reasonably provide.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>Audit-Related Fees</i>.&nbsp;These are fees for assurance and related services that are reasonably related to the performance of the audit or review of the Company&#8217;s financial statements.&nbsp;Such services include accounting consultations, internal control reviews, audits in connection with acquisitions, attest services related to financial reporting that are not required by statute or regulation and required agreed-upon procedure engagements.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>Tax Fees</i>.&nbsp;Such services include tax compliance, tax advice and tax planning.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>All Other Fees</i>.&nbsp;These are fees for other permissible work that does not meet the above category descriptions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such services include information technology and technical assistance provided to the Company.&nbsp;Generally, this category would include permitted corporate finance assistance, advisory services and licenses to technical accounting research software.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">These accounting services are actively monitored (as to both spending level and work content) by the Audit Committee to maintain the appropriate objectivity and independence in the core area of accounting work performed by Ernst &amp; Young LLP, which is the audit of the Company&#8217;s consolidated financial statements.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>Pre-Approval Policy for Audit and Non-Audit Services</i>.&nbsp;In accordance with the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, all audit and non-audit services provided to the Company by its independent auditors must be pre-approved by the Audit Committee.&nbsp;As authorized by that act, the Audit Committee has delegated to the Chair of the Audit Committee the authority to pre-approve up to $25,000 in audit and non-audit services.&nbsp;This authority may be exercised when the Audit Committee is not in session.&nbsp;Any decisions by the Chair of the Audit Committee under this delegated authority will be reported at the next meeting of the Audit Committee.&nbsp;All services reported in the preceding fee table for fiscal years 2018 and 2019 were pre-approved by the full Audit Committee, as required by then applicable law.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company is asking you to vote on the adoption of the following resolution:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">RESOLVED: That the shareholders of the Company ratify the appointment of Ernst &amp; Young LLP as the Company&#8217;s independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending December 31, 2020.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">12</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The affirmative vote of a majority of the votes cast will be necessary to approve this proposal.&nbsp;Abstentions will have no effect on the outcome of this proposal.&nbsp;The shareholder vote on this proposal is advisory and non-binding and serves only as a recommendation to the Board of Directors.&nbsp;If the shareholders do not ratify the appointment of Ernst &amp; Young LLP by the affirmative vote of a majority of the votes cast at the meeting, the Audit Committee will reconsider whether or not to retain Ernst &amp; Young LLP.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:9pt;"><b>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECOMMENDS A VOTE &#8220;</b><b><u>FOR</u></b><b>&#8221; THE ABOVE PROPOSAL.</b></p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:12pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;"><b><a id="Corporate" name="Corporate">Corporate</a> </b><b>Responsib</b><b>i</b><b>lity O</b><b>verview</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Alignment with the best interests of the Company&#8217;s shareholders is at the forefront of Apple Hospitality&#8217;s values. Through strong governance practices, sustainability efforts and social engagement, the Company is committed to aligning its governance practices with the best interests of its shareholders and operating in a manner that minimizes its environmental footprint and increases its social impact. Below are some highlights of the Company&#8217;s initiatives.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p>

<table cellpadding="2pt" cellspacing="0pt" style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; border-left: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">

		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td colspan="2" style="vertical-align: top; width: 20%; border-bottom: thin solid rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-top: thin solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: center;"><b>Governance Practices</b></p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: middle; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: middle; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: middle; width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: center;"><b>Practice</b></p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: middle; width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: center;"><b>Description</b></p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: middle; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: middle; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Annual director elections with majority vote requirements</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">An incumbent director not receiving the majority of the votes cast in an election must tender his or her resignation from the Board</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Independent directors</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">All members of the Audit, Compensation and Nominating and Corporate Governance Committees are independent directors who have access to management and employees</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Board independence</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Five out of eight of the Company&#8217;s directors are independent</p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Chairman of Board and Chief Executive Officer are the only employee directors</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Board diversity</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Two out of eight directors are female</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">

			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Lead independent director</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Lead Independent Director is designated by independent directors, maintains expansive duties to optimize the Board&#8217;s effectiveness and independence, including serving as a liaison to facilitate communications between management and shareholders and the Board</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Separation in leadership structure&nbsp;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Chairman of Board and Chief Executive Officer are separate individuals</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Board self-evaluations</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee oversees an annual self-evaluation of the Board and each committee</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">

		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Succession planning</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">The Board actively monitors the Company&#8217;s succession planning and employee development and receives regular updates on employee engagement, retention and diversity</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Director stock ownership</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Directors are required to own securities of the Company with a value of at least 2 times their annual base cash retainer</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Executive stock ownership</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Executive officers are required to own securities of the Company with a value of at least 5 times (Chief Executive Officer) and 3 times (other executive officers) their annual base salary</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Anti-hedging policy</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Company&#8217;s Insider Trading Policy prohibits directors and employees from engaging in any hedging of Company securities</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Code of business conduct and ethics</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">The Company has a Code of Business Conduct and Ethics that serves as the foundation for how it conducts its business</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<table cellpadding="0pt" cellspacing="0pt" style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; border-left: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">

		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-top: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Incentive-based compensation</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-top: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">80% of 2019 target compensation for executive officers is incentive-based (50% based on shareholder return metrics and 50% based on operational performance metrics)</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Elimination of certain takeover defenses</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt 0pt 22pt; text-align: left; text-indent: -18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Company opted out of the Virginia Stock Corporation Act provisions requiring super majority vote for specified transactions with interested shareholders</p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt 0pt 22pt; text-align: left; text-indent: -18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Company has elected, pursuant to a provision in its bylaws, to exempt any acquisition of its shares from the control share acquisition provisions of the Virginia Stock Corporation Act</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 20%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 80%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 4pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">Accountability to shareholders</p>
