<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:59.25pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="CorporateGovernance" name="CorporateGovernance">Corporate Governanc</a>e, Risk Oversight and Procedures for Shareholder Communications</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><a id="BoardofDirectors" name="BoardofDirectors"><i>Board of Directors</i></a>.&nbsp;The Company&#8217;s Board of Directors has determined that all of the Company&#8217;s directors (and nominees for director), except Mrs. Kristian M. Gathright, Mr. Glade M. Knight and Mr. Justin G. Knight, are &#8220;independent&#8221; within the meaning of the rules of the New York Stock Exchange (&#8220;NYSE&#8221;), including Mr. Bruce H. Matson, who retired in December 2019. In making this determination, the Board considered all relationships between the applicable director and the Company, including commercial, industrial, banking, consulting, legal, accounting, charitable and familial relationships. Although retired from the Company, due to her previous employment by the Company, Mrs. Gathright will not be considered independent for three years from her retirement date.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Board has adopted a categorical standard that a director is not independent (a) if he or she receives any personal financial benefit from, on account of or in connection with a relationship</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">15</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000">
<div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">between the Company and the director (excluding directors&#8217; fees and equity-based awards); (b) if he or she is a partner, officer, employee or managing member of an entity that has a business or professional relationship with, and that receives compensation from, the Company; or (c) if he or she is a non-managing member or shareholder of such an entity and owns 10% or more of the membership interests or common stock of that entity.&nbsp;The Board may determine that a director with a business or other relationship that does not fit within the categorical standard described in the immediately preceding sentence is independent, but in that event, the Board is required to disclose the basis for its determination in the Company&#8217;s then current annual proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">In order to optimize the effectiveness and independence of the Board, the independent directors have designated an independent, non-employee director to serve as the Company&#8217;s Lead Independent Director, which currently is held by Jon Fosheim.&nbsp;See &#8220;Committees of the Board and Board Leadership.&#8221;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><a id="CodeofEthics" name="CodeofEthics"><i>Code of Ethics</i></a>.&nbsp;The Board has adopted a Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for the Company&#8217;s officers, directors and employees, which is available at the Company&#8217;s website, www.applehospitalityreit.com.&nbsp;The purpose of the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics is to promote (a) honest and ethical conduct, including the ethical handling of actual or apparent conflicts of interest; (b) full, fair, accurate, timely and understandable disclosure in periodic reports required to be filed by the Company; and (c) compliance with all applicable rules and regulations that apply to the Company and its officers, directors and employees.&nbsp;Any waiver of the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for the Company&#8217;s executive officers or Board may be made only by the Board or one of the Board&#8217;s committees. The Company anticipates that any waivers of the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics will be posted on the Company&#8217;s website.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="GovernanceGuidelines" name="GovernanceGuidelines">Corporate</a> Governance Guidelines</i>. The Board has adopted Corporate Governance Guidelines that set forth the guidelines and principles for the conduct of the Board of Directors, which is available at the Company&#8217;s website, www.applehospitalityreit.com.&nbsp;The Corporate Governance Guidelines reflect the Board of Directors&#8217; commitment to monitoring the effectiveness of decision-making at the Board and management level and ensuring adherence to good corporate governance principles, all with a goal of enhancing shareholder value over the long term.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="RiskOversight" name="RiskOversight">Risk Oversight</a>.</i>&nbsp;The Board believes that risk oversight is a key function of a Board of Directors.&nbsp;It administers its oversight responsibilities through its Audit Committee, Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and Compensation Committee.&nbsp;All members of each of these committees are independent directors.&nbsp;The entire Board is kept abreast of and involved in the Company&#8217;s risk oversight process.&nbsp;It is through the approval of officers and compensation plans, as well as management updates on property performance, industry performance, financing strategy, acquisitions and dispositions strategy and capital improvements, that the Board has input to manage the Company&#8217;s various risks.&nbsp;Additionally, through the Audit Committee, the Board reviews management&#8217;s and independent auditors&#8217; reports on the Company&#8217;s internal controls and any associated potential risks of fraudulent activities. Through the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee, the Board reviews the Company&#8217;s Corporate Governance Guidelines and related risks.&nbsp;Through the Compensation Committee, the Board oversees risk related to compensation practices with the objective of balancing risk/rewards to overall business strategy.&nbsp;Risk oversight is also one of the factors considered by the Board in establishing its leadership structure.&nbsp;The Company has separated the roles of Chairman and Chief Executive Officer to create a leadership structure that the Board believes strikes the appropriate balance between the authority of those who oversee the Company and those who manage it on a day-to-day basis and also has a Lead Independent Director to optimize the effectiveness and independence of the Board.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="ShareholderComm" name="ShareholderComm">Shareholder Comm</a>unications.</i>&nbsp;Shareholders and other interested parties may send communications to the Board or to specified individual directors.&nbsp;Any such communications should be directed to the attention of the Lead Independent Director at Apple Hospitality REIT, Inc., 814 East Main Street, Richmond, Virginia 23219.&nbsp;The Lead Independent Director will decide what</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">16</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000">
<div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">action should be taken with respect to the communication, including whether such communication should be reported to the full Board.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="ShareOwnership" name="ShareOwnership">Share Ownership</a> Guidelines. </i>The Board believes that equity ownership by directors and executive officers will align their interests with shareholders&#8217; interests. To that end, the Company has adopted formal share ownership guidelines, included in the Company&#8217;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, applicable to all of its directors and executive officers. On an annual basis, the Company evaluates the ownership status of the directors and executive officers. Directors and executive officers are required to own securities of the Company with a value equal to the following multiple of their annual base cash retainer (for directors) or their annual base salary (for executive officers):</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table cellpadding="0pt" cellspacing="0pt" style="width: 50%; text-indent: 0px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 25%; margin-right: 25%;">

		<tr style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 70%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">Directors</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 30%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">2x</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 70%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">Chief Executive Officer</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 30%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">5x</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 70%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">Other executive officers</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 30%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">3x</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">New directors or executive officers are required to comply with the ownership requirements within two years of becoming a member of the Board or an executive officer. All current directors and executive officers currently comply with the ownership guidelines.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee may waive the stock ownership requirements in the event of financial hardship or other good cause.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="Hedging" name="Hedging">Hedging</a> and Pledging of Company Securities</i>.&nbsp;The Company&#8217;s<i>&nbsp;</i>Insider Trading Policy prohibits directors and employees, including the executive officers, from hedging their ownership of the Company&#8217;s stock, including a prohibition on engaging in the following transactions: (i) trading in call or put options involving the Company&#8217;s securities and other derivative securities; (ii) engaging in short sales of the Company&#8217;s securities; (iii) holding the Company&#8217;s securities in a margin account; (iv) other hedging or monetization transactions related to the Company&#8217;s securities, including the use of financial instruments such as prepaid variable forwards, equity swaps, collars and exchange funds; and (v) pledging more than 50% of the number of the Company&#8217;s securities held individually to secure margin or other loans.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="Self-Evaluation" name="Self-Evaluation">Board </a>Self-Evaluation</i>.&nbsp;Pursuant to the Company&#8217;s Corporate Governance Guidelines and the charters of the Compensation, Audit and Nominating and Corporate Governance Committees of the Board of Directors, the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee oversees the annual self-evaluation of the Board and each committee. The self-evaluation requires each director to complete a detailed questionnaire soliciting input on matters such as board structure and composition, committee structure, board and committee meeting conduct, board support, education and board and committee performance.&nbsp;The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee reports the assessments to the Board, and if the Board determines that changes in its governance practices need to be made, management and the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will work with the Board to implement the necessary changes.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9.35pt;"><b><a id="Consideration" name="Consideration">Consideration</a> of Director Nominees</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><a id="DirectorQualifications" name="DirectorQualifications"><i>Director Qualifications</i></a>. The Company believes the Board should encompass a diverse range of talent, skill and expertise sufficient to provide sound and prudent guidance with respect to the Company&#8217;s operations and interests.&nbsp;Each director also is expected to exhibit high standards of integrity, practical and mature business judgment, including the ability to make independent analytical inquiries, and be willing to devote sufficient time to carrying out their duties and responsibilities effectively.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Board has determined that the Board of Directors as a whole must have the right mix of characteristics and skills for the optimal functioning of the Board in its oversight of the Company.&nbsp;The Board believes it should be comprised of persons with skills in areas such as finance, real estate, investment, banking, strategic planning, human resources, leadership of business</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">17</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">organizations, and legal matters.&nbsp;Although it does not have a diversity policy, the Board believes it is desirable for the Board to be composed of individuals who represent a mix of viewpoints, experiences and backgrounds.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">In addition to the targeted skill areas, the Board looks for a strong record of achievement in key knowledge areas that it believes are critical for directors to add value to the Board, including:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="NominationProcedures" name="NominationProcedures">Nomination Procedures</a>.</i>&nbsp;The Board has established a Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee that oversees the nomination process and recommends nominees to the Board. As outlined above, in selecting a qualified nominee, the Board considers such factors as it deems appropriate, which may include the current composition of the Board; the range of talents of the nominee that would best complement those already represented on the Board; the extent to which the nominee would diversify the Board; the nominee&#8217;s standards of integrity, commitment and independence of thought and judgment; and the need for specialized expertise. Applying these criteria, the Board considers candidates for Board membership suggested by its members, as well as management and shareholders.&nbsp;Shareholders of record may nominate directors in accordance with the Company&#8217;s bylaws which require, among other items, notice sent to the Company&#8217;s Secretary not less than 60 days prior to a shareholder meeting that will include the election of Board members.&nbsp;No nominations other than those proposed by the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee were received for the Annual Meeting.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

			<td id=".amt.4" style="width: 15%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 0pt; vertical-align: top; text-align: center;">2</td>
		</tr>

			<td style="width: 15%; vertical-align: top;">&nbsp;</td>

			<td style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 15%; vertical-align: top;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">Nominating and Corporate Governance</p>
			</td>
			<td style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 2%; vertical-align: top;">&nbsp;</td>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Responsibilities are outlined in its written charter that is available at the Company&#8217;s website, www.applehospitalityreit.com, and include oversight of all aspects of the Company&#8217;s corporate governance, director compensation, and nominations process for the Board of Directors and its committees.</p>
			</td>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><a id="BoardLeadership" name="BoardLeadership"><i>Board Leadership</i></a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board recognizes that one of its key responsibilities is to evaluate and determine its optimal leadership structure so as to provide independent oversight of management. The Board understands that there is no single generally accepted approach to providing Board</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">19</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000">
<div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">leadership and the right Board leadership structure may vary as circumstances warrant. Consistent with this understanding, the independent directors periodically consider the Board&#8217;s leadership structure. Currently, the roles of Chairman and Chief Executive Officer are held by different directors.&nbsp;Mr. Glade M. Knight serves as Executive Chairman and Mr. Justin G. Knight serves as Chief Executive Officer. The Board believes that this structure provides the appropriate balance between the authority of those who oversee the Company and those who manage it on a day-to-day basis. The Executive Chairman of the Board presides at all meetings of the shareholders and of the Board as a whole. The Executive Chairman performs such other duties, and exercises such powers, as from time to time shall be prescribed in the bylaws or by the Board.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Additionally, the Board has appointed Mr. Jon A. Fosheim to serve as Lead Independent Director.&nbsp;The Lead Independent Director&#8217;s responsibilities include, among other things, presiding at meetings or executive sessions of the independent directors and non-employee directors, serving as a liaison to facilitate communications between the Chairman, the Chief Executive Officer and other members of the Board, without inhibiting direct communications between and among such persons, and serving as a liaison to shareholders who request direct communications and consultations with the Board.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt 0.1pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="AuditCommittee" name="AuditCommittee">Audit Committee</a> Independence</i>.&nbsp;The Board of Directors has determined that each current member of the Audit Committee is, and Ms. Blythe J. McGarvie during her term on the Audit Committee was, &#8220;independent,&#8221; as defined in the listing standards of the NYSE.&nbsp;To be considered independent, a member of the Audit Committee must not (other than in his or her capacity as a director or committee member, and subject to certain other limited exceptions) either (a) accept directly or indirectly any consulting, advisory, or other compensatory fee from the Company or any subsidiary; or (b) be an affiliate of the Company or any subsidiary.&nbsp;The Audit Committee currently has two members, Mr. Jon A. Fosheim and&nbsp;Mr. L. Hugh Redd, who are &#8220;financial experts&#8221; within the meaning of the regulations issued by the Securities and Exchange Commission.&nbsp;The Company&#8217;s management believes that the combined experience and capabilities of the Audit Committee members are sufficient for the current and anticipated operations and needs of the Company.<b>&nbsp;</b>In this regard, the Board has determined that each Audit Committee member is &#8220;financially literate&#8221; and that at least two members have &#8220;accounting or related financial management expertise,&#8221; as all such terms are defined by the rules of the NYSE.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="BoardMeetings" name="BoardMeetings">Board Meetings</a>, </i><i>Attendance and Related Information</i>.&nbsp;The Board held a total of seven meetings during 2019 (including regularly scheduled and special meetings). It is the policy of the Company that directors should attend each annual meeting of shareholders.&nbsp;All directors at the time of the meeting attended the 2019 Annual Meeting.&nbsp;The Company also expects directors to attend each regularly scheduled and special meeting of the Board, but recognizes that, from time to time, other commitments may preclude full attendance.&nbsp;In 2019, each director attended at least 75% of the aggregate of (a) the total number of meetings of the Board of Directors that were held during the period in which he or she was a director, and (b) the total number of meetings held by all committees of the Board on which he or she served during the period in which he or she served.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><a id="ExecutiveSessions" name="ExecutiveSessions"><i>Executive Sessions</i></a>.&nbsp;The independent members of the Board of Directors meet independently of management and the non-independent directors in executive sessions on a regular basis, presided by the Lead Independent Director.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="a2019Comp" name="2019Comp">2019 Compensation</a> of Directors</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9.35pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The compensation of the directors is reviewed and approved annually by the Board of Directors.&nbsp;During 2019, the directors of the Company were compensated as follows:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt 0.1pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="Reimbursements" name="Reimbursements">Reimbursements</a> to Directors in </i><i>201</i><i>9</i><i>.</i>&nbsp;All directors were reimbursed by the Company for travel and other out-of-pocket expenses incurred by them to attend meetings of the directors and committee meetings and in conducting the business of the Company.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">20</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000">
<div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="Compensation" name="Compensation">Compensation</a> of </i><i>Non-Employee </i><i>Directors</i>. In 2019, the non-employee directors (classified by the Company as all directors other than Mrs. Kristian M. Gathright, Mr. Glade M. Knight and Mr. Justin G. Knight) received (i) a $165,000 annual retainer, with $65,000 paid in cash and $100,000 paid in vested stock grants, paid in quarterly installments, (ii) an annual retainer for the Chair of the Audit Committee of $15,000 (in addition to fees for service on the Company&#8217;s Disclosure Committee) paid in cash in quarterly installments, and (iii) an annual retainer for the Chair of the Compensation Committee, the Chair of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and the Lead Independent Director of $10,000 each, paid in cash in quarterly installments.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">In March 2020, as a result of the coronavirus (COVID-19) situation and associated economic impact to the Company, non-employee directors&nbsp;volunteered to reduce their annual fee rate. The aggregate reduction in fees for the group totals approximately 17%.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="Non-Employee" name="Non-Employee">Non-Employee</a>&nbsp;Director Deferr</i><i>al</i><i> P</i><i>rogram</i><i>.</i> Effective June 1, 2018, the Board of Directors adopted the Non-Employee Director Deferral Program (the &#8220;Director Deferral Program&#8221;) under the Apple Hospitality REIT, Inc. 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan (the &#8220;2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan&#8221;) for the purpose of providing non-employee members of the Board the opportunity to elect to defer receipt of all or a portion of the annual retainer payable to them for their service on the Board, including the portion of the annual retainer amounts payable in cash (including for service as a Chair of a committee of the Board or Lead Independent Director) and the portion of the annual retainer amounts payable in fully vested Common Shares. As specified by the director, the receipt of payment may be deferred until either (i) the date that his or her service on the Board has ended, (ii) a specified date, or (iii) the earlier of the specified date or the date that his or her service on the Board has ended. The deferred amounts will also be paid if, prior to the time specified by the director, the Company experiences a change in control or upon death of the director. For the portion of the director fees payable in shares, the director may elect to defer his or her fees in the form of deferred stock units, and for the portion of the director fees payable in cash, the director may elect to defer his or her fees either in the form of deferred stock units or as deferred cash fees.</p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Under the Director Deferral Program, the Company has established a notional deferral account (for bookkeeping purposes only) for each&nbsp;non-employee director who has elected to participate and all deferred fees are credited to this account, whether in cash or stock, as of the date the fee otherwise would have been paid to the director (the &#8220;Quarterly Deferral Date&#8221;). Deferred fees converted into deferred stock units are credited to the deferral account based on the fair market value of the Company&#8217;s Common Shares on the Quarterly Deferral Date. On each Quarterly Deferral Date, dividends earned on deferred stock units are credited to the deferral account in the form of additional deferred stock units based on dividends declared by the Company on its outstanding Common Shares during the quarter and the fair market value of the stock on such date. Additionally, on each Quarterly Deferral Date, deferred cash fees are credited with an additional deferred cash amount based on the dividends declared by the Company during the quarter on its outstanding Common Shares and the share equivalent, as defined in the Director Deferral Program, of the deferred cash balance from the preceding quarter. Upon the applicable payment date, as described above in the preceding paragraph, any deferred stock units credited to a director&#8217;s deferral account will be settled solely by delivering an amount of the Company&#8217;s Common Shares equal to the number of such deferred stock units, and, with respect to any deferred cash fees credited to the director&#8217;s deferral account, such fees will be paid solely in the form of cash. Directors have no rights as shareholders of the Company with respect to deferred stock units credited to their deferral accounts.</p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">During 2019, four of the non-employee directors elected to participate in the Director Deferral Program by deferring all or a portion of their annual retainer fees in the form of deferred stock units and/or deferred cash fees.</p>

<p style="background-color:#FFFFFF;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><a id="EmployeeDirectors" name="EmployeeDirectors"><i>Employee </i><i>Directors</i></a>.&nbsp; Mr. Glade M. Knight and Mr. Justin G. Knight are employee directors of the Company and through March 31, 2020, Mrs. Gathright was an employee director of the Company. Accordingly, during 2019, they received no compensation from the Company for their services as directors.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>&nbsp;</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i><a id="a_OutstandingStock" name=" OutstandingStock">Outstanding Stock</a> Option Awards</i><i>. </i>In 2008, the Company adopted the Apple REIT Nine, Inc. 2008 Non-Employee Directors Stock Option Plan (the &#8220;Directors&#8217; Plan&#8221;).&nbsp;The Directors&#8217; Plan provided for automatic grants of options to acquire Common Shares.&nbsp;The Directors&#8217; Plan applied to directors of the Company who were not employees or executive officers of the Company.&nbsp;The Directors&#8217; Plan was terminated effective upon the listing of the Company&#8217;s Common Shares on the NYSE on May 18, 2015 (the &#8220;Listing&#8221;). No further grants can be made under the Directors&#8217; Plan, provided however, the termination did not affect any outstanding director option awards previously issued under the Directors&#8217; Plan.&nbsp;Following the termination of the Directors&#8217; Plan, all awards to directors are made under the 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">See &#8220;Ownership of Certain Beneficial Owners and Management&#8221; for the number of outstanding options that were granted to Mr. Glenn W. Bunting under the Directors&#8217; Plan, which are all fully vested, as of the Record Date. Since adoption of the Directors&#8217; Plan, Mr. Bunting has not exercised any of his options to acquire Common Shares. There were no other outstanding option awards granted to directors as of the Record Date. Mr. Bruce H. Matson had 141,465 fully vested options to acquire Common Shares at the date of his retirement which, if not exercised, will expire no later than 36 months following his retirement.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="Audit" name="Audit">Audit</a> Committee Report</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Audit Committee of the Board of Directors is currently composed of three directors.&nbsp;All three directors are independent directors as defined under &#8220;Committees of the Board and Board Leadership&#8212;Audit Committee Independence.&#8221;&nbsp;The Audit Committee operates under a written charter that was adopted by the Board of Directors and is annually reassessed and updated, as needed, in accordance with applicable rules of the Securities and Exchange Commission.&nbsp;The Audit Committee oversees the Company&#8217;s financial reporting process on behalf of the Board of Directors.&nbsp;In fulfilling its oversight duties, the Audit Committee reviewed and discussed the audited financial statements for fiscal year 2019 with management and the Company&#8217;s independent auditors, Ernst &amp; Young LLP, including the quality and acceptability of the accounting principles, the reasonableness of significant judgments, any critical audit matters identified during the audit and the clarity of disclosure in the financial statements.&nbsp;The Audit Committee also reviewed management&#8217;s report on its assessment of the effectiveness of the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting and Ernst &amp; Young LLP&#8217;s report on the effectiveness of the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.&nbsp;Management is responsible for the preparation, presentation and integrity of the Company&#8217;s financial statements,</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">22</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">accounting and financial reporting principles, internal controls, and procedures designed to assure compliance with accounting standards and applicable laws and regulations.&nbsp;Ernst &amp; Young LLP is responsible for performing an independent audit of the consolidated financial statements and the notes thereto in accordance with generally accepted auditing standards.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Audit Committee also has discussed with the independent auditors the matters required to be discussed pursuant to the applicable requirements of the PCAOB and the Securities and Exchange Commission.&nbsp;Additionally, the Audit Committee has received the written disclosures and letter from the independent auditors required by the applicable requirements of the PCAOB regarding the independent auditor&#8217;s communications with the Audit Committee concerning independence and has discussed, with the independent auditors, the independent auditors&#8217; independence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Based on the review and discussions described in this Report, the Audit Committee recommended to the Board of Directors that the audited financial statements be included in the Company&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2019 for filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="Certain" name="Certain">Certain</a> Relationships and Agreements</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company has, and is expected to continue to engage in, transactions with related parties. These transactions cannot be construed to be at arm&#8217;s length and the results of the Company&#8217;s operations may be different if these transactions were conducted with non-related parties. The Company&#8217;s independent members of the Board of Directors oversee and annually review the Company&#8217;s related party relationships (including the relationships discussed in this section) and are required to approve any significant modifications to the existing relationships, as well as any new significant related party transactions. The Board of Directors is not required to approve each individual transaction that falls under the related party relationships. However, under the direction of the Board of Directors, at least one member of the Company&#8217;s senior management team approves each related party transaction.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Mr. Glade M. Knight, Executive Chairman of the Company, owns Apple Realty Group, Inc. (&#8220;ARG&#8221;), which receives support services from the Company and reimburses the Company for the cost of these services as discussed below. Also, an entity controlled by Mr. Knight is currently a member of and Mr. Knight is Chief Executive Officer of Energy 11 GP, LLC and Energy Resources 12 GP, LLC, which are the respective general partners of Energy 11, L.P. and Energy Resources 12, L.P., each of which receive support services from ARG.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;"><i><a id="Cost_Sharing" name="Cost Sharing">Cost Sharing</a> with Related Entities</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><i>&nbsp;</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company provides support services, including the use of the Company&#8217;s employees and corporate office, to ARG and is reimbursed by ARG for the cost of these services. Under this cost sharing structure, amounts reimbursed to the Company include both compensation for personnel and office-related costs (including office rent, utilities, office supplies, etc.) used by ARG.&nbsp;The amounts reimbursed to the Company are based on the actual costs of the services and a good faith estimate of the proportionate amount of time incurred by the Company&#8217;s employees on behalf of ARG. Total reimbursed costs allocated by the Company to ARG for 2019 totaled approximately $1.3 million.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">23</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000">
<div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">As part of the cost sharing arrangement, certain day-to-day transactions may result in amounts due to or from the Company and ARG. To efficiently manage cash disbursements, the Company or ARG may make payments for the other company. Under this cash management process, each company may advance or defer up to $1 million at any time. Each quarter, any outstanding amounts are settled between the companies. This process allows each company to minimize its cash on hand and reduces the cost for each company. The amounts outstanding at any point in time are not significant to either of the companies. As of December 31, 2019, total amounts due from ARG for reimbursements under the cost sharing structure totaled approximately $0.5 million.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The Company, through its wholly-owned subsidiary, Apple Air Holding, LLC, owns a Learjet used primarily for acquisition, asset management, renovation and public relations purposes.&nbsp;The aircraft is also leased to affiliates of the Company based on third party rates, which leasing activity was not significant during 2019.&nbsp;The Company also utilizes aircraft, owned through two entities, one of which is owned by the Company&#8217;s Executive Chairman, and the other, by its Chief Executive Officer, for acquisition, asset management, renovation and public relations purposes, and reimburses these entities at third party rates.&nbsp;Total costs incurred for the use of these aircraft during 2019 were approximately $0.1 million.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">In addition to the appointments described above, the Board approved a change to the title, but not the roles and responsibilities, of Mr. Justin G. Knight. Effective April 1, 2020, Mr. Justin Knight&#8217;s title became Chief Executive Officer.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">Each executive officer is appointed annually by the Board of Directors at its meeting prior to the annual meeting of shareholders. The following table sets forth biographical information regarding the Company&#8217;s executive officers, other than Mr. Glade M. Knight, Executive Chairman and Mr. Justin G. Knight, Chief Executive Officer, who also serve as directors and whose information is provided above in the section titled &#8220;Proposals to be Voted Upon&#8212;Proposal 1. Election of Directors&#8221;:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;text-indent:0;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;border-bottom:solid 1px #000000;;width:24.7%;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Name and </b><b>T</b><b>itle</b></p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 2.7%;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;border-bottom:solid 1px #000000;;width:72.5%;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Business Experience</b><b> (1)</b></p>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;width:24.7%;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Jeanette A. Clarke</b></p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><i>Senior Vice President and Chief Capital Investments Officer</i></p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>Age: </b>38</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;width:2.7%;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;width:72.5%;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0.1pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">Ms. Clarke was appointed Senior Vice President and Chief Capital Investments Officer effective April 1, 2020. Ms. Clarke previously served as Senior Vice President of Capital Investments for the Company since March 2019, and has held various management and senior management positions with the Apple REIT Companies (as described in Note 1 below) since 2012.&nbsp;Ms. Clarke joined the Apple REIT Companies in 2008. Ms. Clarke has been instrumental in the development of the Company&#8217;s capital investments team, fostering valuable relationships with brand, manager and supplier teams, leading strategic capital reinvestment initiatives, and overseeing the Company&#8217;s energy efficiency and sustainability programs.&nbsp;Prior to joining the Apple REIT Companies, Ms. Clarke served as a Senior Financial Analyst at Genworth Financial, and from 2003 until 2008, she served in various roles at Circuit City Stores, Inc., including Accounting Manager of Expense, Service and Advertising Payables. Within the industry, Ms. Clarke serves on the Marriott Owner &amp; Franchise Technology Advisory Council. Ms. Clarke holds a Master of Business Administration degree from Virginia Commonwealth University and a Bachelor of Science degree, Magna Cum Laude, in Business Administration with a concentration in Finance and minor in Economics from Longwood University.</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><b><a id="Compensation" name="Compensation">Compensation</a> Discussion and Analysis</b></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9.35pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 36pt;">The below Compensation Discussion and Analysis reflects the compensation practices and activity prior to the effects of the COVID-19 situation and associated economic impact to the Company. As a result of the dramatic decline in operations of the Company&#8217;s hotels in late March 2020, in addition to the volunteered reduction in annual fees to non-employee directors&nbsp;discussed above, each of the following adjustments to planned 2020 compensation were made:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>

			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Glade M. Knight, the Company&#8217;s Executive Chairman, volunteered to forego his base salary for six months.</p>

			<td style="width:18pt;vertical-align:top;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">&#9679;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;"><i><a id="KeyExecutive_" name="KeyExecutive ">Key Executive </a>Compensation Practices </i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><i>&nbsp;</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">The following is a summary of the Company&#8217;s key practices to align executive compensation with the interests of its shareholders:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:99.9%;text-indent:0;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;">

		<tr>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;width:50%;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><b>What the Company Does</b></p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align: left; text-indent: -18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Annual advisory vote on executive compensation;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Approximately 80% of average executive target compensation for 2019 is incentive-based;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Approximately 75% of executive target incentive-based compensation for 2019 is payable in Common Shares of the Company;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;50% of target incentive-based compensation for 2019 is based on shareholder return metrics;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;50% of target incentive-based compensation for 2019 is based on operational performance metrics;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Compensation Committee comprised entirely of independent directors;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Compensation Committee retains FPL Associates L.P. (&#8220;FPL&#8221;), an independent compensation consultant who advises the committee on a regular basis;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Limited perquisites that are generally on the same terms as other employees and which represent only a small portion of total executive officer compensation;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Stock ownership requirements for executive officers;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Maximum amounts payable for executive incentive compensation awards; and</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Market-aligned severance policy for executives with a double trigger for any change in control payments.</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align:top;width:50%;">
			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;"><b>What the Company Doesn&#8217;t Do</b></p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align: left; text-indent: -18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;No employment contracts with executive officers;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Company Insider Trading Policy prohibits directors and employees from engaging in hedging of Company securities;</p>

			<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;No dividends paid on restricted stock awards unless they vest;</p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align: left; text-indent: -18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;No grants of stock options; and</p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align: left; text-indent: -18pt;">&#9679;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;No supplemental retirement plans.</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;"><i><a id="AdvisoryVote" name="AdvisoryVote">Advisory Vote</a> on Executive Compensation</i><i>&nbsp;</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;"><i>&nbsp;</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;The Company provides its shareholders annually with the opportunity to cast an advisory vote on executive compensation, and in 2019 approximately 93% of the shares voted were in support of the 2018 compensation of the executive officers. The Compensation Committee viewed this advisory vote as an expression by the shareholders of their general satisfaction with the Company&#8217;s</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
<div class="PGFTR" style="text-align: center; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell PGNUM" style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">28</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000">
<div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">executive compensation program. Consistent with the advisory vote of the shareholders at the 2017 annual meeting of shareholders, the Company will hold advisory votes on executive compensation annually until the next say-on-frequency vote is conducted, which will be no later than 2023.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:18pt;"><i><a id="ExecutiveComp" name="ExecutiveComp">Executive Comp</a>ensation</i><i> Summary</i></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9.35pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:36pt;">This Compensation Discussion and Analysis describes the Company&#8217;s executive compensation arrangements for the Company&#8217;s named executive officers for 2019 and explains the structure and rationale associated with each material element of the 2019 compensation arrangements.&nbsp;The named executive officers for 2019 are as follows:</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
